post: {'type': 'con', 'text': 'There are often structurally similar legal compounds which can be researched instead of the illegal variation. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Although social prejudice may remain, addicts could seek help far easier if there were no fear of legal repercussions.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Drug legalization will stimulate local and national economies. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help drive down the profits of drug cartels since people could get their drugs from legal reliable sources. Hence it may force the cartels to offer a purer product or less expensive to remain competitive. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If drugs were legalized, the prison system would be less over-crowded, which is a [significant issue](https://www.prisonpolicy.org/reports/pie2019.html) in the US.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug use is not the same as drug addiction.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Based on countries that have decriminalized drugs like [Portugal](https://borgenproject.org/decriminalization-of-drugs-in-portugal/), drug use has not significantly increased among the poor population, or at all.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalizing marijuana will increase the risk of accidents on the highways \\(and indeed has in [Washington, Oregon and Colorado](http://fortune.com/2018/10/18/legal-marijuana-car-accidents-study/) where it has been legalized\\) causing harm to others.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'High taxes may ensure that a black market for drugs remains with all the dangers it already has. So drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Affordable drugs will more likely lessen the negative impacts of drug use, as overall users would be less likely to abuse substances due to psychological distress caused by financial instability.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Without the effect of the forbidden fruit, drugs would not be 'cool' anymore \\(subcultures, arts, musicians, writers, etc.\\). Removing this effect would minimize the number of people who use drugs because they feel insecure or want to belong in a group."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If recreational drugs were legal, social events such as parties would have more variety. Drug-friendly events would also have no cause for paranoia. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help law enforcement agencies.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug prohibition has been used as a racist policy to mass incarcerate people of color.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The consumption of psychoactive substances creates religious and transcendental [experiences](https://www.sciencealert.com/how-religion-led-to-humanity-s-love-for-drugs): both are a relevant part of human evolution and significantly shaped human culture. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Pharmaceutical companies could double their revenues by selling harmful and addictive drugs to begin with and subsequently curing medication.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug addiction and abuse are more related to mental health than legality. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If an individual is already addicted, that would indicate they already have regular access to the drug.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Even if criminals are able to offer drugs at lower prices, people would turn to legal drugs because they would not risk prison and they would be sure of the quality of what they're buying. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Assuming that drugs will still be legally forbidden for people under a certain age, the distribution points will not be allowed to sell it to children.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If this was true, cartels would already be moving over to newer, patented pharmaceuticals, whose costs of production is dwarfed by market price already.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Legalization of recreational drug use is not necessary for legalization of expanded drug research. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Without effective law enforcement, legalizing drugs might fuel criminal gang's economies \\(e.g., illegal trade\\). That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There will be less smuggling and less drug-caused conflict. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalizing all drugs will lead to much larger societal rifts: Drug usage is higher among the poor and socially marginalized, which in turn makes their condition worse.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is only true in the case of people whose drug use either causes them to become dangerous or interferes with their lives. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legal cultivation/production of psychoactive compounds on the personal or even community scale could eliminate the international black market for them, making society safer for communities.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Established entities selling drugs would almost certainly not engage in gun battles on the streets over "[turf](https://www.urbandictionary.com/define.php?term=Turf)".'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will make it easier for researchers to study how different illicit drugs affect our brain and thereby advance our understanding of neuroscience.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drugs can give individuals false perceptions of reality, inducing potentially negative behaviour.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If legalized, users could be required to carry safe containers for syringes.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many users currently do not properly dispose of their paraphernalia for fear of being caught with it on them, leading to evidence of illegal drug use being disposed of quickly and carelessly.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Drug legalization will stimulate local and national economies. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Nearly all negative effects of addicts on their families are not fueled by the addiction itself, but the fact that the drug they are addicted to is made illegal by the ban on drugs. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "This isn't possible with the most popular date rape drug alcohol, at least not in higher doses, as it's taste is quite unmistakable."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Giving a legal framework to the use of certain drugs may help to prevent the development of infectious diseases.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Government finances from drug legalization have the potential to fund for social welfare if a proper distribution of taxation is ensured.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This is an argument against incarceration for drug related crimes, not for the outright legalisation of drugs. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The evidence provided in this claim stems largely from importing cheaper cigarettes from the rest of Europe to the UK. The difference in quality is probably minimal. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Currently, in many countries, stores which sell age-restricted products such as alcohol have strict regulations in place to ensure the consumer is of appropriate age. The same could be done with other drugs. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Medical professionals have expressed [negative attitudes](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23490450) in treating illegal substance abusers, which subsequently negatively impacts their treatment. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
